Prove the [Doob-Dynkin lemma](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doobâ€“Dynkin_lemma): let `f : X â†’ Y` and `g : X â†’ Z` be such that `g` is strongly measurable with respect to the pullback by `f`. Then if `Z` is nonempty and completely metrizable there exists a measurable function `h : Y â†’ Z` such that `g = h âˆ˜ f`.

---

You shouldn't need the `NeBot` assumption here, if you start your proof with
```
  rcases eq_or_neBot l with rfl | hl
  Â· simp only [limUnder, lim, Filter.map_bot, bot_le]
    exact stronglyMeasurable_const
```
I'm not sure this lemma and the next one belong to this file: they are general results on strongly measurable functions.

It feels really strange to have algebraic assumptions on `Z` here: isn't the theorem true in general? (If you restrict to the closure of the range of `g`, you have a Polish space, so everything should be well-behaved...)

For what it's worth: I managed to replace `[AddZeroClass Z] [ContinuousAdd Z]` with `[Nonempty Z]`, but I had to go back to `MeasureTheory.Function.SimpleFunc` and `MeasureTheory.Function.StronglyMeasurable.Basic` to give alternate versions of `induction` therein, which do not rely on the algebraic structure (basically, you need the propositions to be true on constants and stable under measurable `piecewise`).

Maybe there's something more clever to do, but if needed, I can give the code (which might need some cleaning).

Oh that's interesting! I also managed to get rid of the assumptions using Borel isomorphism theorem, but I would be glad to see your way to compare. I didn't push my code yet because I want to replace the complete metric assumption by a completely metrizable assumption but there is no typeclass for this so I'm working on that.

I've created a fork [D-Thomine/doob_dynkin](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/tree/D-Thomine/doob_dynkin) of your work.

There are three new versions of older lemmas (`induction'` in `SimpleFunc` and `StronglyMeasurable.Basic`, and `exists_eq_measurable_comp'` in `FactorThrough`), and a new basic technical lemma which should go elsewhere (`piecewise_comp` in `FactorThrough`).

Thank you that's great! I think I prefer your approach. Would it be okay for you if I open a PR for the induction on `SimpleFunc` based on your code? Of course I would put you as co-author. Tell me if you prefer to PR it yourself.
Glad it's helpful to you! I'd prefer if you open the PR yourself; it'll be much easier for you to coordinate these lemmas with the remainder of your work.

pullRequest.title: feat: if `g` is measurable wrt to the pullback by `f` then `g` is a measurable function of `f`
